Political Capital: the Hungarian Guard has increased the risk of countries
According to the Risk Analysis Division, the activities of the Hungarian Guard, which was formed last August, with the support of the Jobbik Magyarországert Mozgalom (Movement for a Better Hungary) increase, in several respects, the political risk of Hungary and the region.
In its "risk warning", the society notes that, in relation to the activities of the Hungarian Guard, the greatest political risk is that "in the short term, aggressive ethnic confrontations can occur as a result of the worsening of the already existing ethnic tension between the Tzigan population and non-Tzigan population of Hungary".
The research institute added that the Hungarian Guard's political strategy likely to provoke this situation is the main reason.
As they say, this is due to one of the main shortcomings of Hungarian political actors: "public actors have passed the public debate on the Roma case to representatives of the radical and extreme political groups that have based a political strategy on the dispute between the Tzigans and the Hungarians."
The problem is exacerbated, normal dialogue becomes impossible, extremists are strengthened and the arrival of aggressive conflicts is more likely, they say.
However, according to the research institute, under the influence of the increased attention of Hungarian and international media, the activities of the Hungarian Guard "has significantly deteriorated the image of Hungary abroad, particularly with regard to the country's confidence in stability and democratic maturity."
They recall that as a result of increased publicity given to the reorganisation of the Hungarian radical and extreme right groups since the fall of 2006, many associations have been formed in Hungary since summer 2007 calling themselves the "national self-defence association".
"The common treaty of these meetings is that they are defined as a civil organization while publicly declaring the preparation of their adherents to defence missions (accidents, national defence, defence of the order), armed if necessary, to exceed, by mentioning the inability of the police, the army, otherwise said of the state," they added.
They reported that everything was in line with the method that, based on the support of the political society and the parties, sought to reject different political ambitions in a civil context.
The emphasis on the civil character and status of the association therefore serves only to avoid the legal traps of registering these associations in court, but they are also a political strategy.
The analysis indicates that the activities of the Hungarian Guard are a factor that also increases the risk of neighbourhood relations.
