What kind of insurance do I need?
Car insurance, which covers the driver in the face of possible disasters, involves an important expenditure that will depend on various factors, such as age, sex, the age of driving licence, civil status, the type of vehicle to be insured or the use that is actually made, among others.
Having a car is the main thing.
And it is that choosing the right car insurance is even harder than choosing the vehicle model.
And it's that, choosing the right car insurance is even harder than choosing the vehicle model.
Car insurance is an agreement between an insurance company and the insurer.
This compromise is materialized by an insurance contract, which establishes that the company receives the value of the premium granted and in exchange it becomes responsible for the obligation to pay the compensation in the event of an accident.
The premium is the price of insurance, which is established by taking into account various factors, such as age, sex, age of driving licence, civil status, type of vehicle to be insured or use, among others.
Insurance companies set their prices according to the statistics, so that the more likely an accident is to occur, the higher the rate to be paid.
That is why people over 25 years of age and women must pay lower premiums, as statistics show that these people have a lower rate of ills than they do.
In the same way, using censuses, companies have concluded that married people tend to have fewer accidents than single drivers.
The use of the vehicle will affect the frequency, and therefore the likelihood of an accident.
By increasing frequency the probability increases.
They are many variables that insurers take into account when establishing the premium price.
For this reason, the driver must carefully examine the situation in order to choose the car insurance that suits his profile best.
We will present here the most significant variables when choosing one or the other type of insurance, so that it, in addition to adapting to the characteristics of the insurer, offers a reasonable price.
Young people under the age of 25 must face various disadvantages when entering into a contract with insurance at an affordable price, as can be the low experience in driving and driving licence age.
Although the ideal for being well assured is a risk-free insurance, there are other more economic options.
The most predictable drivers can choose for insurance any risk with franchise, so that they get coverages of insurance at any risk but at a more affordable price.
This form of convention implies that the client pays part of the amount of the disaster.
"The part of the amount of the damage the client will face will be determined according to the value of the premium, which will be higher the amount will be lower," says Luis Noguera, the head of the First Europe insurance intermediary in Spain.
Another option is extended third-party insurance, so that the customer can ensure protection to deal with damage caused to third parties, but for those caused by his own car.
In addition, it would be covered against the flight, the fires and the loss of the vehicle.
A piece of advice.
If you are a 25-year-old, try to be careful and avoid the harms as much as possible, as this will affect the benefit, which can reduce the price of insurance in the future.
A grant is a reduction in the basic rate that the company has.
On the contrary, a penalty is a increase in the basic rate.
"The benefits and penalties will depend on the company and on the benefit of the company.
If the company has had a good year, it will be able to increase the bonuses," explained Noguera.
Over the last 25 years, it becomes easier for drivers to enter into a contract with insurance, as the rate of disasters is reduced by the accumulated experience.
That is why it is preferable to choose insurance at any risk with franchise.
" Normally young people cannot benefit from the experience of the previous accident, " ensures the director of the European company in Spain and adds that the majority of accidents occur during the second year of driving, once the fear of the news has passed. "
However, if the client is married but has not yet had children, it is preferable that he negotiates insurance at any risk, as soon as his economic situation allows him.
Marriages with children are viewed by insurers as people with the lowest rate of disasters, because the majority will be weaker.
In this case, the best insurance would be a risk-free insurance (may be EUR 300), or an extended third-party insurance from the third year of life of the vehicle when the insured person has a high level of funding.
"They have a more uncontracted conduct and they have a greater purchasing power to allow the luxury to assume a more important amount of franchise," judge Luis Noguera.
For pensioners, a risk-free insurance is preferable (being EUR 150), or an extended third-party insurance when the insurer has a high level of bonus.
It must be said that car insurance is something important, not only because it covers the driver in the face of possible disasters, but also because it represents an important expenditure, that is why it is essential to properly study the insurance that we need most according to our personal situation.
